Sentencas: Heterogeneous systems based on the proton-conducting oxide of La0.95Sr0.05ScO3 - delta with Cu, Fe, Ni, Pd, La0.9Sr0.1MnO3 - delta considered as potential materials of solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) electrodes are synthesized.
Titulo: Composite Electrode Materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with the Protonic Electrolyte of La1 - xSrxScO3 - δ

Sentencas: Chemical interaction between individual components of composite materials is studied, dependences of thermal and chemical expansion of the electrolyte and composites are obtained, conductivity of electrodes is measured under the conditions of SOFC operation.
Titulo: Composite Electrode Materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with the Protonic Electrolyte of La1 - xSrxScO3 - δ
